Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Advice on Velks</span><hr size=1> I'm considering running a few Velks raids to see if I can get some Boots of Bladecalling. I've been on one 'pickup' Velks raid where additional people were added a guild raid. The added people were CotH'd in by the mage who had the boots defaulted. We gathered in a room which looked like a small auditorium.<br>
<br>
After being CoTh'd in we buffed and waited while a monk pulled some golems. When it was clear we rushed Velk's in his room and got him over half dead. After this my memory is unclear but I guess I was ressed. (Either I was ressed or was in wave two..can't remember) Everybody medded for awhile and mildly buffed and rushed in again and killed him. The key to that strategy seemed to be how slow he regenerated.<br>
<br>
This was quite some time ago and I'm sure we had at least four or five groups of 55+ people.<br>
<br>
My question is what is a good strategy for running a raid and killing Velks in today's world of level 60+ folks?<br>
<br>
Advice on group compositions, strategy, how to tell if he is up. etc. would be greatly appreciated. I think I can muster at least three groups of 55-62 folks with friends and guildmates and fill in the other slots as needed.<br>
<br>
Elwynd Moonglow<br>
Level 61 Magician<br>
